By Hammed Shittu in Ilorin. Responding, the state governor, Alhaji Abdulrahman Abdulrasaq, stressed the need to adequately equip the various medical centres in the country to stem medical tourism. Represented by his deputy, Mr. Lekan Alabi, the governor  stated that money that would have been used to develop the country was being spent annually by Nigerians for medical treatment overseas. He noted that the health of the people was key to the present administration promsing that the government would fix it hospitals to ensure health service delivery across the State. He  called on the three tiers of government to rise to the occasion to meet the health need of the people. He commended the Nigerian Navy for its support in maintaining peace in the state.